.\" Written by Ali Abdallah (ali.abdallah@suse.com)
.\" ------------------------------------------------------------------
.TH mbimapidle 1 "@DATE@" "mbimapidle (@VERSION@)" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mbimapidle \- execute command on new IMAP messages
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmbimapidle\fR [\fIoptions\fR]
.br
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.P
\fBmbimapidle\fR maintains persistent server connection using IMAP protocol (RFC
2177) IDLE extension and execute sync command on new messages.
.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Display a summary of command line options.
.TP
\fB-v\fR, \fB--version\fR
Display version information.
.TP
\fB-d\fR, \fB--debug\fR
Print debugging messages (default: disabled)
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--foreground\fR
Run in the foreground instead of forking into a background process (default:
run the background)
.
.SH "CONFIGURATION"
The configuration file is mandatory and should be located at
.TP
\fB$XDG_CONFIG_HOME/mbimapidle/mbimapidlerc\fR (usually \fB~/.config/mbimapidle/mbimapidlerc\fR)
.TP
.P
Lines starting with (#) are comments and are ignored. Configuration file is
defined in sections, an optional [general] section and [MailBoxName] section
defining a mailbox to monitor, you can define multiple [MailBoxName] to monitor.

Configuration entries are composed of \fBkey\fR and \fBvalue\fR such as
key="value", \fBvalue\fR is always double quoted.

\fBmbimapidle\fR will refuse to start if the configuration is invalid, you can
reload the configuration by sending SIGHUP to the process. On SIGHUP, if the
loaded configuration is invalid, \fBmbimapidle\fR will go inactive (but will
not exit), until the configuration is adjusted and so another SIGHUP can be
sent to activate back \fBmbimapidle\fR and mailbox monitoring
.
.SS General section [general]
This is an optional section currently controls only daemon verbosity
.TP
\fBverbose\fR
set to \fBtrue\fR to enabled verbosity, default value \fBfalse\fR.  Note
if verbosity is set to \fBfalse\fR, and \fBmbimapidle\fR is run with \fB-d\fR,
\fB--debug\fR you will still get verbose messages.
.SS Mail box section [MailBoxName]
.TP
\fBhostname\fR\f
imap server hostname to connect to.
.TP
\fBusername\fR
username to authenticate with the imap server
.TP
\fBpassword\fR
password to use for authentication.
.TP
\fBpass_cmd\fR
use a custom command to get the password. NOTE: in a mailbox configuration,
you can only set
\fBpassword="PASS"\fR or \fBpass_cmd="PASS_CMD"\fR but not both.
.TP
\fBidle_timeout\fR
According to RFC 2177, a server may consider a client inactive after 30
minutes. \fBidle_timeout\fR instructs \fBmbimapidle\fR after how much time it
should re-new IDLE subscription to the server. Depending on your preferences,
you can set \fBidle_timeout\fR to values between 5 to 29 minutes. (Default value: 10 minutes)
.TP
\fBcheck_certificate\fR
set \fBfalse\fR to disable checking server ssl certification (not recommended).
.TP
\fBport\fR
imap server TCP port to connect to.
.TP
\fBtls_type\fR
Specify ssl connection type, \fBnone\fR, \fBssl\fR or \fBstarttls\fR. If not
specified
\fBssl\fR is the default on port 993
\fBstarttls\fR is the default on port 143.
Setting it to \fBnone\fR disable ssl encryption and so username and password
will be communicated with the server plaintext, only use this mode if YOU KNOW
WHAT YOU ARE DOING (for example your are using a encrypted tunnel).
.TP
\fBauth\fR
\fBplain\fR sends credentials in plaintext, it is safe when \fBtls_type\fR is
configured to \fBssl\fR or \fBstartssl\fR.
\fBXOAUTH2\fR modern authentication mechanism mainly by Gmail and Microsoft®
Outlook/Office 365, it requires OAuth 2.0 access token, rather than a password.
Depending on the OAuth imap server, so you should use a custom password command
to supply \fBpass_cmd\fR to supply in the password.
.TP
\fBselect\fR
mailbox dir to watch, normally you don't have to change this, the default value
"INBOX" issufficient in most cases.
.TP

For a sample configuration file, please checkout out:
.TP
\fB@CONF_EXAMPLE@\fR
.
.SH AUTHOR
Ali Abdallah (ali.abdallah@suse.com)
